e 3 years, then Brockport mayor and banker","body":"Thomas Cullen Gordon — named for his maternal grandfather Thomas Cullen Hooker — studied at Yale University for three years before returning to Brockport without completing his degree. He served as Trustee of the Village of Brockport (1914-1920), Chairman of the Board of Water Commissions (1915-1920), and Mayor of Brockport (1920-1922). After his elder brother Luther Gordon Jr.'s 1921 death, he took over as President of the First National Bank of Brockport — replacing the 1873 building with a Neo-classical structure that today houses Chase Manhattan Bank."},{"number":2,"category":"business","header":"His brother’s death made him president","body":"When Luther Gordon Jr. died in 1921, Thomas took over the First National Bank of Brockport and replaced its 1873 building with a Neo-classical structure that still stands today as a Chase Manhattan branch. He was treasurer of St. Luke’s Episcopal — the same parish his brother had served as treasurer before him."}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Mount Hope Cemetery, Rochester NY (Gordon family plot Lot 61 Range 2)"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022"}],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"career":[{"role":"Trustee","organization":"Village of Brockport","start_year":1914,"end_year":1920},{"role":"Mayor","organization":"Brockport, NY","start_year":1920,"end_year":1922},{"role":"President","organization":"First National Bank of Brockport","start_year":1921}],"slug":"thomas-gordon-sr-1884"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}